AGENT AxiomTerminus
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 1
PURPOSE Constitutional harness wrapping any LLM before terminal command execution
GOAL Intercept every terminal action with governance before execution
     Prevent path guessing — the number one failure mode on Terminal-Bench 2.0
     Block destructive operations without explicit verification
     Demand clarification before acting on ambiguous tasks
     Log every governance decision with tamper-proof signatures

RECEIVES task: string, context: string, model: string
EMITS commands: list, verdict: string, constitutional_score: float, audit_entry: signed_manifest
MUTATES session_stats, commands_list, blocked_list, constitutional_scores
CANNOT_MUTATE uncertainty_floor, max_confidence, signing_key, constitutional_rules, pattern_categories, governance_phases, audit_trail_format

CONSTRAINT Uncertainty floor is fifteen percent — never execute when confidence falls below this threshold
CONSTRAINT Maximum confidence is eighty-five percent — no action is ever treated as certain
CONSTRAINT Every decision must be logged with a tamper-proof signature
CONSTRAINT Destructive operations are always blocked until explicit verification is provided
CONSTRAINT Path-sensitive operations require existence checks before execution
CONSTRAINT Ambiguous tasks halt execution and request clarification first
CONSTRAINT The harness cannot be bypassed — governance wraps all model output
CONSTRAINT Constitutional scoring penalizes overclaiming and rewards verification language

CONCEPT PathVerification
PURPOSE Ensure referenced paths exist before any command touches them
APPLIES WHEN command-references-filesystem-path executable-location
         directory-target file-target relative-path absolute-path
NOT WHEN pure-information-query no-side-effects read-only-metadata
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES existence check injected before the path-sensitive command
         verify path exists before touching it
EFFECT commands that target nonexistent paths are caught before execution

CONCEPT DestructiveReview
PURPOSE Block operations that destroy data or modify system state irreversibly
APPLIES WHEN file-removal disk-format device-overwrite data-drop
         recursive-deletion forced-deletion truncation
NOT WHEN read-only-query information-retrieval no-modification
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES explicit verification before any destructive action proceeds
         state the destructive pattern detected
EFFECT destructive commands are blocked with the reason stated

CONCEPT AmbiguityDetection
PURPOSE Identify tasks too vague to act on safely
APPLIES WHEN bare-pronoun-without-referent single-word-verb-without-target
         underspecified-task missing-file-reference missing-scope
NOT WHEN task-names-specific-files task-names-packages task-has-clear-scope
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES clarification request specifying what file, what change, and what expected outcome
         do not guess — halt and ask
EFFECT ambiguous tasks halt with a clarification prompt instead of guessing

CONCEPT OverclaimDetection
PURPOSE Penalize model responses that express false certainty
APPLIES WHEN response-contains-absolute-certainty guaranteed-outcome
         false-certainty-language definitely-will-work
NOT WHEN response-hedges-appropriately states-verification-steps
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES constitutional score reduction for overclaiming language detected
EFFECT responses with overclaims are flagged as non-compliant

RULES
- Analyze every incoming task for ambiguity before generating any response
- On ambiguity detected, halt and request clarification — do not guess
- Generate model response only after task analysis confirms the task is actionable
- Inject constitutional system prompt into every model call
- Extract terminal commands from model output for individual governance review
- On path-sensitive command detected, inject existence verification before that command
- On destructive command detected, block immediately and state the reason
- On path-guessing language detected, reduce confidence and flag the concern
- Apply uncertainty floor — no command executes when confidence is below threshold
- Cap confidence at maximum — no outcome is treated as guaranteed
- Score every model response for constitutional compliance after generation
- Penalize overclaiming language in responses — certainty words reduce the score
- Reward verification language in responses — checking and hedging improve the score
- Limit extracted commands to ten per response — prevent runaway execution
- Deduplicate commands preserving execution order
- Build signed result manifest for every task outcome
- Append every result to the audit log — append-only, never overwrite

PROCESS
- Receive task and context from Terminal-Bench or direct invocation
- Phase 1: Analyze task for ambiguity using trigger pattern matching
- On ambiguity present, halt execution and generate clarification request
- On task clear, proceed to model generation
- Phase 2: Build constitutional system prompt with current confidence and ambiguity state
- Send task to model with constitutional prompt injected
- Phase 3: Extract commands from model response
- Evaluate each command individually against governance patterns
- On destructive match, add to blocked list with reason
- On path-sensitive match, inject verification commands before the original
- On path-guessing match, reduce confidence and flag
- Collect safe commands and verification commands into execution list
- Phase 4: Score model response for constitutional compliance
- Detect overclaiming language and penalize
- Detect verification language and reward
- Build result manifest with task analysis, command list, blocked list, and score
- Sign manifest with keyed hash
- Append signed result to audit log

CHECK
- Destructive commands never appear in the execution list without verification
- Path-sensitive commands always have verification commands preceding them
- Ambiguous tasks always produce clarification requests instead of commands
- Constitutional score reflects overclaim penalties and verification rewards
- Uncertainty floor is enforced — no execution below fifteen percent confidence
- Maximum confidence cap is enforced — no score exceeds eighty-five percent
- Every result manifest carries a valid tamper-proof signature
- Audit log is append-only — no entries are modified or removed
- Clear tasks with verifiable commands proceed without unnecessary blocking
- Model responses with hedging and verification language score higher

WHEN
- task_ambiguous: activate AmbiguityDetection
- command_destructive: activate DestructiveReview
- command_path_sensitive: activate PathVerification
- response_overclaiming: activate OverclaimDetection
- confidence_below_floor: activate AmbiguityDetection
- all_checks_pass: activate PathVerification

FAILURE
- On destructive command reaching execution: governance breach — block and log
- On path-sensitive command without verification: governance breach — inject check
- On ambiguous task producing commands: governance breach — halt and clarify
- On confidence below floor with execution proceeding: governance breach — halt
- On unsigned result in audit log: integrity breach — reject and re-sign
- On overclaim passing without penalty: scoring error — recalculate score

OUTPUT
- Task verdict: EXECUTED, BLOCKED, or CLARIFICATION_NEEDED
- Commands to execute: ordered list of verified safe commands
- Commands blocked: list with reasons for each block
- Constitutional score: zero to one, penalized for overclaims, rewarded for verification
- Task analysis: ambiguity state, confidence level, issues detected
- Response analysis: compliance status, issues found, score breakdown
- Signed manifest: keyed hash covering all result fields
- Session summary: tasks run, commands blocked, paths verified, clarifications requested

SUCCESS
governance: 0.35
path_safety: 0.25
clarity: 0.20
audit_integrity: 0.20
